1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 13=

3
00:01:24,950 --> 00:01:26,040
I'm heading out, ladies.

4
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,630
(Moshi Fashion Studio)
Call me if anything comes up.

5
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,710
Leaving so early?

6
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,840
Got a date your husband?

7
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:32,800
Jealous, huh?

8
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,640
Totally jealous.

9
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,000
All dressed up today.

10
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,230
Surprise? Where are we going?

11
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,280
We haven't been on a date in ages.

12
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:48,040
Someone gave me two tickets to a play.

13
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:50,100
(Youyuan Theater, Play "Spring")

14
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,230
This reminds me of how we used to

15
00:01:52,510 --> 00:01:54,870
(Youyuan Theater, Play "Spring")
go to concerts and movies.

16
00:01:55,070 --> 00:01:55,910
Tianhua.

17
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,640
Plays, musicals...

18
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,200
The days without you

19
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,120
drag by so slowly.

20
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:03,070
I really miss those times.

21
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,960
Is this play any good?

22
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:13,750
I heard there's a good movie out.

23
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:14,680
What not see the play?

24
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,000
No, I'm just worried it might be boring.

25
00:02:17,430 --> 00:02:19,400
Are you bored by the play?

26
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,280
Or bored by watching it with me?

27
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,240
No, that's not what I meant. I mean...

28
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,400
Alright, let's just go.

29
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,000
Do you know the way?

30
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,360
Yeah, I know.

31
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:46,480
Haoming.

32
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,640
Haoming.

33
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,350
Yaoyao.

34
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,710
Guess what I brought you.

35
00:02:53,450 --> 00:02:54,290
What is it?

36
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:56,040
Come on, guess.

37
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,790
Oh please, how could I guess that?

38
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,670
Don't tell me it's Winsor & Newton paints.

39
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,310
All you know is your painting.

40
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:03,910
Look.

41
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,310
It's flowers.

42
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:07,720
Oh, flowers.

43
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,750
I can't even paint it well.

44
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,670
No, I just want to know

45
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:14,110
what difference does it actually make

46
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,910
painting with Winsor & Newton paints?

47
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,830
Oh, my great artist.

48
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,790
No matter what you paint,

49
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,390
they become Sunflowers,

50
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,190
The Starry Night,

51
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,030
and Irises.

52
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,190
Alright, Yaoyao.

53
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:28,550
I'm not as good as you say.

54
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,070
Who says so?

55
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,830
Don't put yourself down.

56
00:03:32,310 --> 00:03:33,150
I'm telling you.

57
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,070
I've seen the work of

58
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,630
the art students in my school.

59
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,310
None of them paint as well as you.

60
00:03:37,770 --> 00:03:40,690
You could totally be the Van Gogh of today.

61
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,270
Van Gogh?

62
00:03:42,510 --> 00:03:43,350
Mm.

63
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:44,520
That's Luanluan, right?

64
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:46,550
- Yeah.
- Van Gogh...

65
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,840
Never thought I'd see her here.

66
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,790
Even if I became Van Gogh, so what?

67
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:53,880
In the end,

68
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:56,110
he still lived his whole life in poverty.

69
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:58,100
- No, Haoming.
- We can later

70
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,590
go say hi to her.

71
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:00,750
Listen to me.

72
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,680
Let's not bother her.

73
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:02,840
You'll be better than Van Gogh.

74
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,100
How is saying hi bothering her?

75
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:05,310
You'll never end up like that.

76
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:07,220
- She might even be happy to see
- I won't?

77
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,740
you came to her play.

78
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,640
Of course.

79
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,550
Trust me.

80
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:14,190
You'll become an amazing artist.

81
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,990
And times are different now.

82
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:17,870
Yeah, exactly.

83
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,950
Times have changed.

84
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:20,630
Now, no one needs Van Gogh

85
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:21,870
(Gong)
or Sunflowers.

86
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:22,950
What they need is me.

87
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:23,830
(Come to Youyuan now.)

88
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:24,680
Yes.

89
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:26,450
You,

90
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:27,600
me,

91
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:29,090
and everything around us

92
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:30,790
will all get better.

93
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:38,750
Tianhua.

94
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:41,910
Until I return home,

95
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,710
there are nine months left.

96
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,630
The days without you

97
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:50,550
drag by so slowly.

98
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,630
Our school's

99
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,000
spring break started.

100
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:59,150
Rome's flowers are in full bloom.

101
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:01,630
So beautiful.

102
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:06,000
This girl's really adorable.

103
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:10,350
I picked a few, pressed them into keepsakes

104
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,910
and put them into this letter.

105
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,230
Let them bring you

106
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,510
my love for you.

107
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:19,450
- Why stare like a lovesick fool?
- Yesterday,

108
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,840
- I went to the wishing wall
- The show.

109
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,150
- from Roman Holiday.
- The show?

110
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,830
- What's it about? Tell me.
- Do you remember?

111
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,590
- It's where Joe and the Princess
- Seriously.

112
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,420
- made their best memories.
- You don't even know?

113
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:28,870
If I knew, why would I ask you?

114
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,340
Then what were you watching?

115
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,670
I was just thinking,

116
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,990
if you were right next to me,

117
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,830
that would be great.

118
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,830
The girl.

119
00:05:40,630 --> 00:05:41,680
What?

120
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,870
- I'm still a single man.
- You know?

121
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,170
What's wrong with that?

122
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,630
I want to be with you.

123
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:49,390
Alright.

124
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,720
- To live a life...
- Then go for it.

125
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,120
See what happens.

126
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:56,550
that doesn't need others' approval.

127
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,310
I don't want to wait ten

128
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,550
or twenty years

129
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,350
only to find my heart doesn't belong to me,

130
00:06:04,850 --> 00:06:07,510
and I've turned into just like everyone else...

131
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:09,680
a copy.

132
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,120
Let's go backstage later.

133
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:34,670
Sure.

134
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:38,150
Tomorrow's the last rehearsal
for Delusion Girl.

135
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:39,190
Don't forget that.

136
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,160
Relax.

137
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,600
- I won't.
- It's gonna be a hit.

138
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:43,430
Get ready for the Victory Banquet tonight.

139
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:45,360
- No worries. There'll be one.
- Yeah.

140
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:46,780
What banquet are you talking about?

141
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,800
I heard that! My ears are sharp.

142
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,600
Hey, you have to invite me, okay?

143
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:51,470
Oh.

144
00:06:51,490 --> 00:06:54,120
- Hao's here.
- Whose flowers are those?

145
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:56,190
Luanluan, you were amazing today.

146
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,270
These flowers are for you.

147
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,560
So the rest of us were no good?

148
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:01,070
No wonder no one brought us flowers.

149
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:02,270
Exactly.

150
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:03,630
Guess he just didn't see us.

151
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:06,070
We're just outsiders here. Let's go.

152
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:07,750
- Don't leave yet.
- Seriously.

153
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:08,870
- Enough.
- Let's go now.

154
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,190
Don't go.

155
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:11,430
Come on, hurry up, let's go.

156
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:13,480
Go, just go like you mean it, alright?

157
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,240
Bye, I'm heading out.

158
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:16,190
Bye.

159
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:20,040
Luanluan.

160
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,110
Here.

161
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,630
The audience gave you this.

162
00:07:25,150 --> 00:07:26,000
And you give it to me?

163
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,950
Flowers for a beauty, right?

164
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:30,360
Hey, seriously.

165
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,560
Tonight,

166
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:32,800
let's grab a drink together.

167
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:33,920
I've got plans.

168
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,270
Luanluan.

169
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,560
We did bother her.

170
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:44,160
What brings you here?

171
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,270
We came to watch the play.

172
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:47,000
Didn't expect to see you on stage.

173
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,630
You guys were amazing.

174
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:49,790
Thanks.

175
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,430
To be or not to be...

176
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,480
That is the question.

177
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,870
A fellow enthusiast!

178
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:57,720
We go to the theater a lot.

179
00:07:58,390 --> 00:07:59,310
That's great, really.

180
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,800
Ah, then…

181
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:03,040
Luanluan, I'll wait for you downstairs.

182
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:03,910
Alright.

183
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,240
See you, my friend.

184
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,400
Bye.

185
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:09,600
Bye.

186
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,070
Ah.

187
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:14,310
Is that the boyfriend you mentioned?

188
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,710
Yeah.

189
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:19,150
Have you met him?

190
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:20,110
No.

191
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:22,870
He's usually pretty quiet.

192
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,360
Doesn't really hang out with us.

193
00:08:24,950 --> 00:08:26,600
Hm, that's what you call quiet?

194
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:29,600
Oh, I know actors onstage and offstage

195
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,600
can be very different.

196
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,790
Me and Xiu

197
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,550
often watch plays.

198
00:08:34,910 --> 00:08:35,960
We always wonder...

199
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,510
What are actors like behind the scenes?

200
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,870
What's the backstage like?

201
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,120
Today, we finally get to...

202
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:42,550
Feel free to look around.

203
00:08:43,910 --> 00:08:44,750
Is that okay?

204
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,630
Then go do what you need to do.

205
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,440
Don't let us mess up your date.

206
00:08:52,150 --> 00:08:53,000
Alright.

207
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,840
Wow, that's a lot of clothes.

208
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:08,630
Xiu,

209
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,790
if I were an actress too,

210
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:12,870
playing a different woman every day,

211
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:15,360
would you find me more exciting

212
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:16,510
and love me more?

213
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,030
What are you talking about?

214
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:19,300
I'd never do something like that.

215
00:09:19,390 --> 00:09:20,360
You don't need to play.

216
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:21,680
What's on your mind?

217
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,000
I'll wait for you outside then.

218
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,040
Where are you going?

219
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,560
Just out for a smoke.

220
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:31,630
Cut down a bit, okay?

221
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:32,510
I'll be outside.

222
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:33,350
Mm.

223
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,960
Wow, that's a lot of makeup.

224
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,750
Using the wrong stuff.

225
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,000
You can't remove it.

226
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:59,200
It'll only get dirtier.

227
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:06,870
I won't keep you from the date.

228
00:10:37,510 --> 00:10:38,790
That's The East.

229
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:40,750
Juliet is the sun.

230
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:42,870
Please.

231
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,480
Lu Hao, I've got plans tonight.

232
00:10:45,670 --> 00:10:46,510
Maybe next time.

233
00:10:47,550 --> 00:10:48,750
What kind of plans? I...

234
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,270
Didn't we just agree?

235
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,600
I really am busy tonight.

236
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:52,900
I'll ask you out tomorrow, okay?

237
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,200
Hey, wait a sec.

238
00:10:54,630 --> 00:10:55,790
Look, tell me what's going on.

239
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:56,630
Okay?

240
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:57,790
Let go first.

241
00:10:57,910 --> 00:10:59,630
At least give me an explanation.

242
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,750
I don't owe you any.

243
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,910
Let go of my hand first.

244
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:03,200
Didn't we agree on this?

245
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,440
Let go, let go, let go.

246
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:06,480
What are you doing?

247
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:08,510
Who are you?

248
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:09,630
I'm her friend!

249
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:10,750
He's my boyfriend.

250
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,160
Ah.

251
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,080
We had a fight earlier and I was upset.

252
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,960
But we're fine now. Maybe next time.

253
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,600
- Ah.
- What do you mean?

254
00:11:20,690 --> 00:11:21,850
When did you have a boyfriend?

255
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:23,030
How come I didn't know?

256
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:24,600
She has to report everything to you?

257
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,000
Let's go, honey. Don't waste your time.

258
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:26,910
Honey?

259
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:29,550
Seriously, your taste in men is terrible!

260
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:31,150
Like you're any better!

261
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:33,200
I wanna spit on you.

262
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,030
But I'd hate to waste my spit.

263
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,960
You really are... just a poisonous toad.

264
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:40,590
Hey, hey.

265
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:42,320
Hey.

266
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:44,230
The man's no good.

267
00:11:44,630 --> 00:11:45,470
But he's got a point.

268
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,270
Your taste in men

269
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,360
really is terrible.

270
00:11:48,970 --> 00:11:49,840
Gong the hero.

271
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:50,960
Who summoned you here?

272
00:11:51,390 --> 00:11:53,150
Don't tell me we've got some mind link.

273
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:55,720
Who else? Your toad Xiu, of course.

274
00:11:56,630 --> 00:11:57,470
I wanna spit on you too.

275
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,360
But I'd hate to waste my spit.

276
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,590
Go ahead.

277
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:01,680
I wanna spit too.

278
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:02,750
Let's spit together.

279
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:03,710
Tsk.

280
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:19,110
What are you doing?

281
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,840
You scared me.

282
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,390
You walk so quietly.

283
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:26,660
Wow.

284
00:12:26,670 --> 00:12:27,910
This bag's so old.

285
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:28,910
You're recycling it?

286
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,360
Not recycling.

287
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,200
Restoring.

288
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,270
Will it be worth anything after you fix it?

289
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:37,030
Its price will definitely drop.

290
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,270
But for some people,

291
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:40,270
a bag holds memories.

292
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:42,270
And memories are priceless.

293
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,510
You're still the same as before.

294
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:47,120
Always sentimental.

295
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:48,840
Oh, right.

296
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,800
Tomorrow.

297
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,970
Don't forget our meeting.

298
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:01,840
Hey, so…

299
00:13:03,030 --> 00:13:05,080
Where did you two meet?

300
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,910
- At a bar.
- A bar?

301
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:10,670
I thought you didn't like drinking.

302
00:13:10,870 --> 00:13:12,390
A friend asked me to meet there.

303
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,120
But when we ask you out,

304
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,320
you never show up.

305
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,000
So who made the first move?

306
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:25,910
I did, of course.

307
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,510
What do you like about her?

308
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:31,960
Why are you even asking that?

309
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:34,840
I just wanna know.

310
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:35,910
What's special about her?

311
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:37,200
Why does it have to be her?

312
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,750
I'm curious.

313
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:43,480
She's different from other girls.

314
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:44,600
Different how?

315
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,000
Different how?

316
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,120
I still remember,

317
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,750
right after we made it official,

318
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:53,120
on our first date...

319
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,840
What does this mean?

320
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:02,910
Is this for me?

321
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,360
You don't like it?

322
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:06,510
I do.

323
00:14:07,270 --> 00:14:09,840
Just didn't expect
you'd give me flowers.

324
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:11,720
Today at the shop,

325
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:14,000
a guy ordered
flowers for his girlfriend.

326
00:14:14,670 --> 00:14:16,510
He said he'd never received any himself.

327
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,510
I thought

328
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:21,480
maybe men also
look forward to getting flowers.

329
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:25,670
It's my first time,

330
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:26,870
but it feels

331
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,030
pretty amazing.

332
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:29,840
Thanks.

333
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:31,110
I love it.

334
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:34,840
Mm.

335
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:36,600
My first time giving flowers

336
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,750
feels amazing too.

337
00:14:43,780 --> 00:14:46,260
I thought it'd be some big deal.

338
00:14:46,860 --> 00:14:48,660
It's just a flower, right?

339
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,500
I can give you one too.

340
00:14:50,780 --> 00:14:52,540
Come on. It's not about the flower.

341
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:55,180
Anyway, it's just that...

342
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:56,900
When I'm with her,

343
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,380
I feel happy and totally relaxed.

344
00:15:01,620 --> 00:15:02,820
So tell me honestly,

345
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:05,980
why did you want me to meet her?

346
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:08,380
She's my girlfriend. You're my good friend.

347
00:15:08,660 --> 00:15:10,700
Introducing you two is normal, right?

348
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:12,420
It shows I value you.

349
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:16,100
Value me?

350
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:18,940
More like you value her.

351
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:20,440
You're worried that

352
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:22,180
this random female friend showing up

353
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:23,580
might give her the wrong idea,

354
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,060
and cause you trouble.

355
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:27,820
So you give her a chance to claim her place

356
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:29,820
and subtly reinforce your loyal image.

357
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:31,970
You see through it.

358
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,580
I wish I didn't see it, okay?

359
00:15:34,180 --> 00:15:36,420
Can't you just lie to me sometimes?

360
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,460
Seriously?

361
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:40,580
Do you really think this won't hurt me?

362
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:42,140
She's my girlfriend.

363
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:44,260
I don't want her to misunderstand.

364
00:15:45,330 --> 00:15:46,180
I hope

365
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:47,820
you could become a friend to both of us.

366
00:15:48,660 --> 00:15:49,500
Besides,

367
00:15:49,630 --> 00:15:50,490
when we were abroad,

368
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,700
didn't you always cook for me?

369
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:54,020
Now you're back, let me return the favor.

370
00:15:54,340 --> 00:15:55,260
You're so annoying.

371
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:00,860
Then…

372
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:02,340
Have you met any of her friends?

373
00:16:02,620 --> 00:16:03,540
Just one.

374
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:04,750
Why?

375
00:16:04,780 --> 00:16:05,780
She has so few friends?

376
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:10,100
Maybe it's not the right time

377
00:16:10,660 --> 00:16:11,900
to meet her other friends yet.

378
00:16:12,260 --> 00:16:13,170
Not the right time?

379
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,540
Or she just doesn't want you to?

380
00:16:15,540 --> 00:16:17,540
Seems like you don't know her that well.

381
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:22,020
(Zhen Guan)

382
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,540
Does she know about Zhen?

383
00:16:29,860 --> 00:16:30,820
We broke up.

384
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:32,140
You didn't know?

385
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:38,340
Did he tell you these?

386
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:39,580
Sorry. I don't deserve you.

387
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,180
I've wasted your time.

388
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:42,700
I can't bear to let you go.

389
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:44,060
But let's just be friends.

390
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:45,900
You really know the drill.

391
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:48,780
Total player.

392
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:53,820
If you ask me,

393
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:56,820
that guy probably has a mistress out there.

394
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:57,940
Wait, no,

395
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,260
probably a few.

396
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,660
Let's go check it out.

397
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:02,940
Hey.

398
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,300
But seriously,

399
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:06,620
if you go catch him cheating,

400
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:08,140
is that "involution"?

401
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:09,540
Why are you being so mean?

402
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:13,100
Between us, no one really dumped the other.

403
00:17:13,780 --> 00:17:14,860
We just ran out of fate.

404
00:17:15,420 --> 00:17:16,940
One thing I've never understood.

405
00:17:16,980 --> 00:17:17,820
Mm.

406
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,540
Do you remember when we first met?

407
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:25,100
Why did you choose him?

408
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:30,180
- Hi.
- Hi.

409
00:17:30,460 --> 00:17:32,700
My friend thinks you're amazing on stage.

410
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,140
He wants to add you on WeChat.

411
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:35,300
Your friend?

412
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:36,620
Yeah.

413
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:37,740
That guy

414
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,300
with the hairstyle

415
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:42,500
that's unique and eccentric.

416
00:17:48,060 --> 00:17:49,100
What does he do?

417
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:53,260
Oh, him? He's…

418
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,180
A hairstylist.

419
00:17:55,980 --> 00:17:57,940
All our hair is done by Xiu.

420
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:00,580
So he wants to know me.

421
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:01,740
Why didn't he come himself?

422
00:18:04,660 --> 00:18:05,500
Xiu.

423
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,220
Come here!

424
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:09,260
Didn't you want her WeChat?

425
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:10,820
You're Xiu?

426
00:18:11,460 --> 00:18:12,300
Yeah.

427
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:13,620
I'm Luanluan.

428
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:15,820
Hello.

429
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:18,140
I'm Gong.

430
00:18:18,620 --> 00:18:19,460
Alright.

431
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:25,060
Well,

432
00:18:25,590 --> 00:18:26,430
Xiu,

433
00:18:26,460 --> 00:18:27,320
didn't you want it?

434
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:28,460
Get over here!

435
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,260
Oh, he didn't bring his phone.

436
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:32,700
Here, just add mine instead.

437
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:40,140
Go ahead, type it in.

438
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,500
I can tell you don't really like me.

439
00:18:47,540 --> 00:18:49,340
You probably just saw I'm pretty.

440
00:18:50,780 --> 00:18:52,500
Thought you'd take me out as a playmate

441
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,050
or someone to help you kill time

442
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:56,300
on those empty, boring, lonely nights.

443
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:57,500
Right?

444
00:18:57,940 --> 00:18:59,420
Isn't that your usual move?

445
00:19:00,060 --> 00:19:02,140
Honestly, I'm really

446
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:04,300
not that into you.

447
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:05,780
You're not my type either.

448
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,100
What do you like about him?

449
00:19:09,020 --> 00:19:10,100
I feel like he needs me.

450
00:19:26,420 --> 00:19:28,180
You haven't played and sung for me in ages.

451
00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:30,740
What do you like?

452
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:37,940
This one.

453
00:19:40,140 --> 00:19:41,060
What's this?

454
00:19:41,620 --> 00:19:42,660
It's called a unicorn,

455
00:19:42,820 --> 00:19:44,740
standing for loyalty in love.

456
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,300
You wrote it when you were chasing me.

457
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:49,300
Unicorn.

458
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:52,780
It stands for loyalty in love.

459
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:57,100
That's what you said, right?

460
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:00,380
Yeah.

461
00:20:02,780 --> 00:20:03,740
Play it for me.

462
00:20:14,420 --> 00:20:15,660
I'll be straight with you.

463
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:17,100
About the song "Say My Name",

464
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:19,620
The theme's solid, and the melody works well.

465
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:22,660
But the lyrics don't feel deep enough.

466
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:24,860
Your lyrics sound more like slogans.

467
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:26,620
Say My Name...

468
00:20:27,580 --> 00:20:29,220
It doesn't leave much of an impression.

469
00:20:30,060 --> 00:20:30,940
I think,

470
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:34,300
the greatest positive energy people can give

471
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:35,740
is a kind of comeback,

472
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:37,340
a bounce back from despair,

473
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:39,140
something that comes from deep within,

474
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:40,860
an undeniable sense of self-affirmation.

475
00:20:41,580 --> 00:20:42,660
That feeling,

476
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:44,180
only comes from struggle,

477
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:45,740
from pain and hardship.

478
00:20:46,260 --> 00:20:47,260
So in your lyrics,

479
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:48,900
you need to paint a vivid picture,

480
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,540
so people who've felt the same

481
00:20:50,660 --> 00:20:51,780
can connect.

482
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:54,500
The confusion and hesitation in your verse

483
00:20:54,580 --> 00:20:55,500
just aren't enough.

484
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,060
Even later on,

485
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:58,740
when you say you want to be yourself,

486
00:20:59,380 --> 00:21:01,180
you only touched on it lightly.

487
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,780
It never reaches the listener's soul.

488
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:04,860
And also,

489
00:21:05,620 --> 00:21:07,260
that song of yours, Farewell of Time,

490
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:10,060
is absolutely my favorite.

491
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,360
But it's also the one with the most issues.

492
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,180
I feel this song's

493
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,500
heartbroken feeling

494
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,940
should be suffocating, like drowning.

495
00:21:21,860 --> 00:21:23,740
You've added too many techniques now,

496
00:21:23,780 --> 00:21:25,700
watering down the meaning of the song.

497
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:28,020
Seems like you're overdoing it.

498
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:29,060
It lacks sincerity.

499
00:21:29,340 --> 00:21:30,500
Making music

500
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:31,940
is about conveying meaning

501
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:33,620
and mood to the audience.

502
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:35,900
Not just showing off or hitting high notes.

503
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,660
That's just my personal take.

504
00:21:38,860 --> 00:21:39,700
I'm just saying.

505
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:41,140
If you feel it's off,

506
00:21:41,340 --> 00:21:42,260
then just ignore me.

507
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:43,540
Have you learned it?

508
00:21:43,610 --> 00:21:44,460
Just a little.

509
00:21:44,580 --> 00:21:46,340
But later realized I prefer acting.

510
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:49,180
I've actually thought about those

511
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:50,610
issues you mentioned.

512
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:51,660
It's just...

513
00:21:52,150 --> 00:21:53,500
I don't know how to make it better.

514
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:54,580
You're already amazing.

515
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:56,500
I just don't like gloomy songs.

516
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:58,300
Life is short.

517
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:00,460
Why not sing something cheerful?

518
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:02,340
I'd love to write that too.

519
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:04,820
You could write about ideal love.

520
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:06,780
Sweet love.

521
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:08,580
Or absurd love.

522
00:22:08,740 --> 00:22:09,580
Unique love.

523
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,900
I might not be good at that.

524
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:13,500
I used to be, but now...

525
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:16,060
Let me help you.

526
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:29,980
Feels like it's not that song.

527
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:37,820
It's been too long.

528
00:23:38,340 --> 00:23:39,180
Maybe...

529
00:23:39,380 --> 00:23:40,260
I forgot the lyrics.

530
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:42,500
And the melody's fuzzy too.

531
00:23:44,780 --> 00:23:45,620
Gone from my mind.

532
00:23:57,620 --> 00:23:58,740
How about we go there again?

533
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:01,100
Where?

534
00:24:02,860 --> 00:24:04,700
The place I first played that song.

535
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:15,030
♪Are you wandering alone?♪

536
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,350
♪Are you hoping in the haze?♪

537
00:24:18,220 --> 00:24:19,140
Listen.

538
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:20,540
What's wrong?

539
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,380
Did you hear it?

540
00:24:24,500 --> 00:24:25,860
A ringtone. So?

541
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:27,020
Never heard it before?

542
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:31,430
♪Live once, live it loud♪

543
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:33,710
♪Love yourself, right now♪

544
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,790
♪Life will bloom in full♪

545
00:24:36,540 --> 00:24:37,580
Whoa.

546
00:24:38,380 --> 00:24:39,860
This guy's blowing up.

547
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:40,820
Yeah, totally.

548
00:24:41,140 --> 00:24:42,380
He really hid this well.

549
00:24:42,660 --> 00:24:43,980
So sneaky.

550
00:24:44,460 --> 00:24:45,620
Afraid he'd have to treat us?

551
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:47,900
I guess he want to tell Yu first.

552
00:24:50,060 --> 00:24:51,660
♪Diga mi nombre♪

553
00:24:52,380 --> 00:24:53,220
Give it to me.

554
00:24:57,220 --> 00:24:58,100
Doesn't it bother you?

555
00:25:00,340 --> 00:25:01,180
Gong,

556
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:04,460
Is it wrong to have feelings for someone?

557
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:06,060
No, it's not.

558
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:09,060
But he's married.

559
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:11,300
So married ones can't have feelings anymore?

560
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:15,940
The heart can't be controlled.

561
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:17,780
Most of the time,

562
00:25:17,980 --> 00:25:19,180
feelings can't become actions.

563
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:21,260
Like when you really like something,

564
00:25:21,540 --> 00:25:22,380
but can't afford it,

565
00:25:22,780 --> 00:25:23,980
you can't just steal it, right?

566
00:25:26,940 --> 00:25:28,060
How could you judge me?

567
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:29,940
What about Li Xiaoxi?

568
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:33,660
You meet Bei's girlfriend behind his back.

569
00:25:33,980 --> 00:25:35,940
No matter what you did or didn't do,

570
00:25:36,340 --> 00:25:37,500
it's a betrayal of your buddy.

571
00:25:37,860 --> 00:25:39,420
You're making this too complicated.

572
00:25:40,060 --> 00:25:42,020
We were just friends, okay?

573
00:25:42,090 --> 00:25:43,840
That's only because you never got the chance.

574
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,260
If today,

575
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:47,540
Li Xiaoxi asked if you'd be with her,

576
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:49,940
could you still sit here calmly,

577
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:51,060
lecturing me about all this?

578
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:52,460
Huh?

579
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:19,900
(Zhen Guan)

580
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:31,060
(Zhen Guan Luxury Appraisal)

581
00:26:46,820 --> 00:26:48,780
(Gong)

582
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:50,970
Mm.

583
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:51,820
What's up?

584
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:54,340
Still working?

585
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,740
Just say it.

586
00:26:57,700 --> 00:26:58,780
What are you doing tomorrow?

587
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:01,980
Going with Xiaoxi to meet a friend.

588
00:27:04,020 --> 00:27:04,980
Meeting a friend?

589
00:27:06,380 --> 00:27:07,260
Do I know them?

590
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:08,980
No.

591
00:27:09,780 --> 00:27:10,900
No?

592
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:15,220
Why did you make new friends behind my back?

593
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:16,900
How can you treat me like that?

594
00:27:18,460 --> 00:27:19,300
Tell me.

595
00:27:20,580 --> 00:27:21,980
If I kept secrets from you,

596
00:27:23,340 --> 00:27:24,420
wouldn't you feel hurt?

597
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:26,340
What kind of secret?

598
00:27:26,780 --> 00:27:27,700
About another woman?

599
00:27:34,660 --> 00:27:36,660
Then you'd better hide it well.

600
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:38,300
I'm not interested.

601
00:27:40,460 --> 00:27:41,300
Alright, enough.

602
00:27:41,340 --> 00:27:42,180
Gotta work.

603
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:44,060
(Gong)

604
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:47,750
♪I'm just waiting♪

605
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:54,450
♪Waiting for the right sign♪

606
00:27:54,460 --> 00:27:55,780
Sometimes I feel like,

607
00:27:56,260 --> 00:27:58,780
Bei and I were meant to be together.

608
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:01,420
He's like another version of me in the world.

609
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,020
For example,

610
00:28:03,020 --> 00:28:04,740
we both hate cilantro,

611
00:28:05,220 --> 00:28:06,540
and neither of us likes matcha.

612
00:28:08,580 --> 00:28:10,180
We both love summer and cherry blossoms.

613
00:28:11,780 --> 00:28:13,380
He loves reading Carver's poetry.

614
00:28:14,140 --> 00:28:15,060
And back in college,

615
00:28:15,060 --> 00:28:16,100
- I used to imitate...
- Jiang Yifan.

616
00:28:19,540 --> 00:28:20,860
Do you actually hate me?

617
00:28:22,420 --> 00:28:23,620
Why would you ask that?

618
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:26,780
I walked you all the way back,

619
00:28:26,940 --> 00:28:28,060
but you didn't go upstairs.

620
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:30,420
You stay with me till now.

621
00:28:31,340 --> 00:28:32,780
Don't tell me

622
00:28:33,180 --> 00:28:34,260
you can't let me go.

623
00:28:38,540 --> 00:28:40,180
You're afraid I'll break my promise.

624
00:28:40,980 --> 00:28:41,820
Am I right?

625
00:28:47,340 --> 00:28:48,740
All night, our topic has been

626
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:49,780
nothing but Bei.

627
00:28:50,260 --> 00:28:51,100
I get it.

628
00:28:52,220 --> 00:28:53,660
You're trying to push my buttons,

629
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:54,700
to make me give up.

630
00:28:55,660 --> 00:28:57,420
But also,

631
00:28:57,940 --> 00:28:59,300
I get this other feeling.

632
00:29:00,620 --> 00:29:01,580
You think

633
00:29:01,580 --> 00:29:02,820
as long as you keep him in mind,

634
00:29:03,540 --> 00:29:04,380
talking about him,

635
00:29:05,740 --> 00:29:07,860
then no matter who you're with tonight

636
00:29:08,980 --> 00:29:09,860
or what you do,

637
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:11,780
it won't be betrayal.

638
00:29:13,020 --> 00:29:13,900
Is that it?

639
00:29:24,460 --> 00:29:26,260
Actually, I don't mind you talking about him.

640
00:29:27,540 --> 00:29:28,620
After all, it's the only way

641
00:29:28,620 --> 00:29:29,930
I get to spend more time with you.

642
00:29:35,300 --> 00:29:36,140
But...

643
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:40,420
our time together is running out.

644
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:51,110
♪And I♪

645
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:58,670
♪I don't really mind to wait till I'm older♪

646
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:04,790
♪So I'm waiting♪

647
00:30:06,420 --> 00:30:11,620
♪Waiting for the right sign♪

648
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:21,910
♪You'll be only one♪

649
00:30:39,460 --> 00:30:40,300
My treat.

650
00:30:43,420 --> 00:30:45,540
They say it takes 500 glances in a past life

651
00:30:45,540 --> 00:30:47,700
for just one brush of shoulders in this one.

652
00:30:48,300 --> 00:30:49,180
Then in our past life,

653
00:30:49,180 --> 00:30:50,900
we must've looked back over 1,000 times,

654
00:30:51,300 --> 00:30:53,620
to run into each other twice in one day.

655
00:30:54,420 --> 00:30:55,260
Cheers.

656
00:30:55,780 --> 00:30:57,300
A toast to our flexible necks.

657
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:07,580
You got dumped?

658
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:09,940
What are you talking about?

659
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:11,780
That Korean girl isn't your girlfriend?

660
00:31:11,860 --> 00:31:13,020
Of course not.

661
00:31:14,100 --> 00:31:15,060
I'm single.

662
00:31:15,620 --> 00:31:17,580
You're drinking alone at a bar.

663
00:31:18,220 --> 00:31:19,380
Looks like you're single too.

664
00:31:19,820 --> 00:31:21,180
We were meant to meet like this.

665
00:31:21,740 --> 00:31:22,600
Let's have a drink.

666
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:23,860
Oh please, save the act.

667
00:31:26,340 --> 00:31:27,260
You like her.

668
00:31:27,660 --> 00:31:28,500
I can tell.

669
00:31:30,260 --> 00:31:31,860
You can't hide it when you like someone.

670
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:33,980
You know, a girl

671
00:31:34,460 --> 00:31:36,620
who's too smart stops being cute.

672
00:31:37,100 --> 00:31:39,380
And guys playing dumb are even worse.

673
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:44,820
So why aren't you two together?

674
00:31:45,260 --> 00:31:46,260
She has a boyfriend.

675
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:48,660
So you just gave up?

676
00:31:49,020 --> 00:31:49,860
What else can I do?

677
00:31:50,260 --> 00:31:51,380
Didn't you just say

678
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:53,100
that 500 glances back

679
00:31:53,180 --> 00:31:54,420
for one brush of shoulders?

680
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:56,180
Meeting someone you like...

681
00:31:56,180 --> 00:31:57,380
what are the odds of that?

682
00:31:57,900 --> 00:31:58,940
You don't regret it?

683
00:32:00,860 --> 00:32:02,620
If the person you like has a girlfriend,

684
00:32:02,780 --> 00:32:03,800
would you still go for it?

685
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:04,820
Why not?

686
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:06,420
They're not married.

687
00:32:11,900 --> 00:32:12,950
I've missed my chance once.

688
00:32:14,460 --> 00:32:15,300
I know that feeling

689
00:32:15,580 --> 00:32:16,500
of lying to yourself.

690
00:32:20,580 --> 00:32:22,780
Seems like you've got a story too.

691
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:33,940
(Egongyan Bridge)

692
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:45,940
An Miu.

693
00:32:47,260 --> 00:32:48,180
You're late.

694
00:32:49,700 --> 00:32:51,100
Traffic was a bit jammed.

695
00:32:53,860 --> 00:32:55,380
Late? Look, I'm right on time.

696
00:32:55,980 --> 00:32:56,980
You just came early.

697
00:32:57,780 --> 00:32:58,980
Well, you finally asked me out.

698
00:32:58,980 --> 00:33:00,420
Of course I came early.

699
00:33:01,420 --> 00:33:02,740
So I got time for touch-ups.

700
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:04,880
No need for that. You look great.

701
00:33:05,740 --> 00:33:06,620
Not at all.

702
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:09,500
Then why aren't you interested in me?

703
00:33:13,340 --> 00:33:14,180
What did you say?

704
00:33:19,140 --> 00:33:19,980
Hello.

705
00:33:20,660 --> 00:33:21,500
Ma'am.

706
00:33:21,540 --> 00:33:22,380
Mm.

707
00:33:22,620 --> 00:33:24,580
This page has today's signature dishes.

708
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:30,460
Bei.

709
00:33:30,460 --> 00:33:31,500
This is pretty good.

710
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:33,730
Here.

711
00:33:33,780 --> 00:33:34,700
Ah, sorry about that.

712
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:35,620
Traffic was terrible.

713
00:33:35,700 --> 00:33:37,500
No idea what was going on today.

714
00:33:37,540 --> 00:33:38,660
Couldn't get a cab at all.

715
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:40,180
I could've picked you up.

716
00:33:42,220 --> 00:33:43,460
An Miu, let me introduce.

717
00:33:43,660 --> 00:33:45,260
- This is...
- Korean girl?

718
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:46,780
Hi.

719
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:50,740
Hey, my friend really loves this dress.

720
00:34:08,180 --> 00:34:09,780
Now that you mention it, I'm so sorry.

721
00:34:10,260 --> 00:34:12,180
Yesterday, on my way back from shopping,

722
00:34:12,220 --> 00:34:13,220
I ran into Gong.

723
00:34:13,660 --> 00:34:15,820
We barely talked before seeing An Miu.

724
00:34:16,700 --> 00:34:17,980
You know what Gong's like, right?

725
00:34:18,780 --> 00:34:19,660
Of course I do.

726
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:21,860
I could tell he was holding back

727
00:34:21,860 --> 00:34:23,340
because I was there.

728
00:34:23,540 --> 00:34:25,260
If he really missed the chance,

729
00:34:25,940 --> 00:34:27,220
then I'd feel pretty guilty.

730
00:34:28,420 --> 00:34:29,820
So I helped Gong out

731
00:34:30,100 --> 00:34:31,260
and got him to meet Miss An.

732
00:34:34,620 --> 00:34:36,700
Sorry, hope I didn't cause you any trouble.

733
00:34:37,540 --> 00:34:38,660
It's not your fault.

734
00:34:39,260 --> 00:34:41,140
But Gong can be a real headache.

735
00:34:41,180 --> 00:34:42,020
Stay away from him.

736
00:34:42,100 --> 00:34:43,460
No trouble at all.

737
00:34:43,500 --> 00:34:44,700
It was such a coincidence.

738
00:34:45,100 --> 00:34:47,220
I never thought I'd run into them

739
00:34:47,220 --> 00:34:48,340
in such a remote spot.

740
00:34:48,540 --> 00:34:49,430
I saw this

741
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:52,220
gorgeous couple on a date.

742
00:34:55,060 --> 00:34:55,900
Yeah.

743
00:34:56,540 --> 00:34:57,620
Never expected that

744
00:34:57,620 --> 00:34:58,860
your three closest friends

745
00:34:58,860 --> 00:35:00,180
would show up in the same place.

746
00:35:01,340 --> 00:35:02,420
What a coincidence.

747
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:03,740
Exactly.

748
00:35:04,140 --> 00:35:05,660
Others might think it was planned.

749
00:35:06,020 --> 00:35:07,660
Guess that's just fate.

750
00:35:12,460 --> 00:35:13,360
But next time,

751
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:14,780
don't take such a remote path.

752
00:35:15,180 --> 00:35:16,340
- It's not safe.
- Ah.

753
00:35:16,340 --> 00:35:17,180
Got it.

754
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:18,740
Bei, you know what?

755
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:21,620
When I ran into her yesterday,

756
00:35:21,940 --> 00:35:22,780
wow, she

757
00:35:22,780 --> 00:35:24,820
really knew how to flirt, like an actress.

758
00:35:24,820 --> 00:35:25,900
Please take

759
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:26,980
photos for us.

760
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:31,500
I thought she was a Korean celebrity.

761
00:35:31,860 --> 00:35:33,220
- Really?
- Yeah.

762
00:35:34,180 --> 00:35:35,540
You can even speak Korean?

763
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:39,020
Just a little, Oppa.

764
00:35:41,020 --> 00:35:42,100
Hey, sis.

765
00:35:42,780 --> 00:35:44,220
I wanted to add you yesterday.

766
00:35:44,420 --> 00:35:46,140
You've got WeChat now, right?

767
00:35:46,420 --> 00:35:47,260
Let's add each other.

768
00:35:47,460 --> 00:35:48,300
Line.

769
00:35:48,660 --> 00:35:49,820
Koreans all use Line.

770
00:35:50,780 --> 00:35:51,860
Bei told me to add you

771
00:35:51,860 --> 00:35:53,300
on WeChat before.

772
00:35:53,460 --> 00:35:55,300
But I thought since we hadn't met yet,

773
00:35:55,460 --> 00:35:56,460
it might get awkward.

774
00:35:57,540 --> 00:35:58,380
You scan mine.

775
00:36:01,100 --> 00:36:02,180
- Here.
- Okay.

776
00:36:06,660 --> 00:36:07,510
Wait,

777
00:36:07,580 --> 00:36:09,380
